🚫Propylparaben
🚫Isobutylparaben
🚫Butylparaben
🚫Isopropylparaben 
🚫Methylparaben
🚫Ethylparaben 

The long chain parabens propyl- and butyl- are both linked to high estrogenic activity in multiple research studies and should be absolutely avoided.

Happy Earth Day! 🌎💛 Red Rock Canyon is one of my top 5 favorite things about living in Las Vegas. It’s only minutes from the house and we love coming here as often as we can. So much beauty everywhere you go.✨💛✨

My tips for Red Rock Canyon: 

💛 If you’re with people who can’t hike or it’s 110* you can drive the loop and it’s just as beautiful as the hikes. Make sure you give yourself about 45min… once you’re in you’re in and there’s no turning around. 

💛 No reservations needed before 8am. Bonus: May 31st no reservations needed at all for the park until October. 🙌

💛Make sure to let someone know you’re going before you go into the canyon. There’s little to no reception in most areas inside the park. 

💛 Bring proper hiking shoes for most trails. 

💛 Bring water & sunscreen 

👉 I would avoid bringing your dog to Oak Creek Canyon. There’s lots of cholla (jumping cactus🌵) on this trail. There’s plenty of other dog friendly trails to explore without all the cacti.

👉Stay on the trail 🤣

#redrockcanyon #happyearthday #ilovelasvegas #oakcreekcanyon

For the best facial dry brushing experience, follow these easy tips.💛👇

Start with cleansing because brushing with dirt on your face is a no no. 🧖‍♀️

Next, massage the lymph nodes to make sure everything drains properly. 💆‍♀️

Third, stretch the neck for even more drainage. 💛

Finally, use light strokes to move the lymph on the face. No need to go hard here. Light pressure is all you need.✨

That’s it! Just 2-3 minutes 2x a week is all you need for face brushing. 💛

Save & practice @gratifiedsoul’s favorite facial dry brushing routine for glowing skin 😍

Facial dry brushing has a wealth of benefits, like:
🩸 Increasing circulation,
💧 Boosting lymphatic drainage, and
✨ Gently removing dead skin cells (which can accumulate more during cold, dry seasons, causing your complexion to look dull).

Pro Tip: Remember to start at your chin & work your way up, using gentle upward strokes. Once you work your way up, do the same strokes going back down to help your lymphatic system drain.
